ce:section.ce:para:
Based on the structure and reactive functional groups of PEDOT:PSS, a S, N co-doped CNDs was devised by a hydro-thermal synthesis as dopant to improve the electronic and structural homogeneity of PEDOT:PSS in inverted PHJ PSCs. The uncombined sulfur double bond of S,N co-doped CNDs caused by thiourea introduces more microcosmic interstice inside the CNDs with abundant functionalized amidogen. The functionalized CNDs can band the superfluous PSS and remove the insulating component from PEDOT:PSS mixture, resulting in the conductivity and hole extraction capability enhancement. The optimized PSCs demonstrate a very promising air stability and photovoltaic performance including an open-circuit voltage (V

                        oc
                     ) of 1.01 V, a short-circuit current (J

                        sc
                     ) of 22.6 mA cm−2, and a fill factor (FF) 79.06%, yielding a PCE of 18.03%. This research proposes a new strategy to improve the quality of PEDOT:PSS using targeted synthesis of functionalized CNDs in allusion to the material inherent defect.
